[1]
Date: Fri, 14 May 2004 14:03:37 -0400
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Yahoo News, UK [edited]
<http://uk.news.yahoo.com/040514/323/etlcl.html>


Canada free of Asian style bird flu : officials
------------------------------------------------------------
Tests have proved that a new variant of bird flu discovered in western
Canada is not the strain of the disease that killed 24 people in Asia,
officials said. The Canada Food Inspection Agency had said this week that
investigators might have found an H5 strain of the virus on a farm in the
Fraser Valley, near Vancouver, and were testing to see if it was the H5N1
variant found in Asia.

But it said Friday, those fears were groundless.

"Further testing has revealed that geese on a Fraser Valley farm were not
infected with either H5 or H7 avian influenza," the agency said in a
statement. "There is strong evidence indicating the geese were exposed to
the H6 avian influenza virus. The H6 virus is not associated with serious
animal or human illness."

Further tests were talking place to define the exact type of virus found in
the geese and in some ducks on the farm.

Canadian authorities have ordered a massive cull of about 19 million
poultry in the Fraser Valley area, the centre of an outbreak of H7N3 bird
flu which has so far been found on 40 farms and 10 small poultry operations.

